summary:
Starrcade was an annual professional wrestling super‑card held from 1983‑2000. First carried on closed‑circuit TV and later on pay‑per‑view, it was staged by the NWA and, later, WCW. Continuing Jim Crockett Promotions’ tradition of Thanksgiving/Christmas shows at Greensboro Coliseum, Starrcade events included:
• Starrcade 1985 – the third annual show promoted by JCP under the NWA banner;
• Starrcade 1987 – the fifth annual JCP/NWA show; 
• Starrcade 1997 – the fifteenth annual event, presented as a pay‑per‑view.
